                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-277-off1416 t18310908-277-crimeloc1419"></join> and I felt a pull at my coat pocket - on turning round, I saw the prisoner close to my elbow; I accused him of taking my handkerchief out of my pocket - he asked what handkerchief I meant - I said, "The handkerchief you took from my pocket" - he said he had not got it; I took him to the station-house, and on the road he gave it me.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did I not give it you immediately you asked for it? A. No; I accused him of it three times before he gave it me.</p>
               <p>NEAL LYNCH. I am a Policeman. The prisoner was brought to the station-house, about half-past eight o'clock, with the handkerchief; Ladd gave the same account as he has now.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
